ans who, quite literally, made history. In these troubled times, it will surely inspire a new generation of scholars and activists.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aChicago (Ill.)-History-20th century. 0aGay liberation movementzIllinoiszChicago. 0aGay liberation movement-Illinois-Chicago. 0aGaysxHistoryzIllinoiszChicago. 0aGaysxSocieties, etczIllinoiszChicago. 0aGayszIllinoiszChicagoxHistory. 0aGayszIllinoiszChicagoxSocieties, etc. 0aGays-Illinois-Chicago-History. 0aGays-Illinois-Chicago-Societies, etc. 0aSexual minority communityzIllinoiszChicago. 0aSexual minority community-Illinois-Chicago. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  achicago, community, queer, gay, lqbtq, lgbt, archive, transgender, gender nonconforming, politics, culture, race, academia, religion, visibility, pride, inclusion, identity, recognition, equality, protests, resistance, political movements, tolerance, acceptance, homosexuality, same sex, liberation, radicals, stonewall, step may, amigas latinas, activism, james darby, hiv, aids, military, gary nepon, artemis singers, metis press, dennis halan, march, glaad, peg grey, sports, nonfiction, history, sexuality, janet soule.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226727677423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226727677/original  a978-3-11-069309-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles